Databook

Databook: Variables

  • yelp: csv dataset
  • yelp_clean: yelp + tokenized df
  • yelp_negative: 1 star review df
  • yelp_positive: 5 star review df
  • yelp_class_complete: 1 - 5 star review df
  • yelp_class_boundary: 1 and 5 star review df
  • X_complete: yelp_class['text'] for the complete df
  • y_complete: yelp_class['stars'] for the complete df
  • X_boundary: yelp_class['text'] for the reduced df
  • y_boundary: yelp_class['stars'] for the reduced df

Databook: Variables

  • X_train: training set for respective yelp_class['text'] df subset
  • X_test: testing set for respective yelp_class['text'] df subset
  • y_train: training set for respective yelp_class['stars'] df subset
  • y_test: testing set for respective yelp_class['stars'] df subset
  • classifier_nb: naive bayes classifier
  • classifier_linear: linear SVM classifier
  • classifier_linear_library: linear SVM classifier from LinearSVC library
  • classifier_logistic_regression: logistic regression classifier
  • t0, t1, t2: timestamp

Databook: Variables

  • prediction: set of predictions for a unique classifier
  • time_train: training time
  • time_predict: prediction time
  • score: accuracy for a unique classifier
  • cm: convolutional matrix for a unique classifier
  • fpr: false positive rate
  • tpr: true positive rate
  • roc_auc: area under curve of a ROC for a unique classifier

Databook: Functions

  • convert(x): convert json line into csv return: csv object
  • text_process(text): preprocess text string return: array of words
  • convert_review_large_csv(override): convert full yelp json dataset
  • clean_dataset(yelp): retype df, append 'length' and 'tokenized' return: processed dataset
  • create_class(yelp, boundary): generate df from yelp dataset based on the boundary boolean return: yelp df
  • generate_X_y(yelp_class): generate 'text' and 'stars' df return: 'text' and 'stars' df
  • bow_transformer(X): bag of words transformer return: bow fit and transformed df

Dataset

Cleaned Dataset

def clean_dataset(yelp):
    yelp['text'] = yelp['text'].astype(str)
    yelp['length'] = yelp['text'].apply(len)
    yelp['tokenized'] = yelp.apply(lambda row: text_process(row['text']),
      axis=1)
    yelp.to_csv('review_small_clean_tokenized.csv', encoding='utf-8',
      index=False)
    
    return yelp

Stars Count

As shown the reduced dataset (10,000 yelp datapoints) is offset to higher stars, so we should expect to see more errors in correctly predicting negative reviews over positive reviews.
